About the job
\U0001f5c2 We’re Hiring: Cloud Engineer (Entry-Level / Associate)
 \U0001f552 Employment Type: Full-Time
 \U0001f4bc Level: Entry-Level / Associate
We’re looking for a motivated and detail-oriented Cloud Engineer to join our growing technology team. In this role, you will support the design, deployment, and maintenance of cloud-based infrastructure and services. You’ll collaborate with development, DevOps, and IT teams to ensure scalable, secure, and high-performing cloud environments. If you’re passionate about cloud technologies and eager to build your career in modern infrastructure, we’d love to hear from you!
\U0001f3af Key Responsibilities
Assist in deploying, managing, and monitoring cloud infrastructure across platforms such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.
Support the configuration and maintenance of cloud services, including compute, storage, and networking.
Help implement infrastructure-as-code (IaC) using tools like Terraform or CloudFormation.
Monitor system performance and troubleshoot cloud-related issues.
Collaborate with development teams to support CI/CD pipelines and application deployments.
Ensure cloud environments follow security best practices and compliance standards.
Assist in optimizing cloud resources for cost, performance, and scalability.
Document cloud architecture, processes, and configurations.
Stay up to date with emerging cloud technologies and industry best practices.
\u2705 Requirements
Basic understanding of cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud).
Familiarity with networking concepts (DNS, VPC, load balancing).
Knowledge of operating systems, especially Linux.
Basic scripting skills (e.g., Python, Bash, or PowerShell).
Understanding of containers (Docker) and orchestration tools (Kubernetes) is a plus.
Familiarity with version control systems like Git.
Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a team environment.
Relevant coursework, certifications, or internship experience is preferred.
\U0001f31f What We Offer
A collaborative and innovative work environment.
Hands-on experience with modern cloud technologies and infrastructure.
Opportunities for professional growth and cloud certification support.
Exposure to real-world cloud projects and scalable systems.
Supportive team culture with mentorship and knowledge sharing.
Competitive salary and benefits package.

